This paper deals with the robustness of sampling algorithms, which is a fundamental problem in data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of information theory (cs.IT) to analyze the problem and the potential for attacks on the sampling algorithm (cs.CR). Finally, the paper proposes modifications to the sampling algorithm to improve its robustness, which is a common theme in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
